                            <comment id="15205826" author="paulk" created="Tue, 22 Mar 2016 05:29:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually, if you are referring to the &lt;tt&gt;query&lt;/tt&gt; method variants, then I believe this is a documentation copy-n-paste error. The point of those variants is to minimise adding overhead (creating wrapper objects etc.); otherwise, &lt;tt&gt;eachRow&lt;/tt&gt; or similar could be used. So, instead I suggest we fix the doco.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15223098" author="jwagenleitner" created="Sun, 3 Apr 2016 01:51:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for reporting the issue, I&apos;ve &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/groovy/commit/9dcd0c8997ad143918a3e54a1c4313dcafc6cf1d&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;updated the javadocs&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
